1. Open VS Code
2. Extensions view or Ctrl+Shift+X
3. Search for "Python" and install the extension by Microsoft.
4. Open the project folder.
5. Run terminal, Ctrl+Shift+`
6. Create virtual environment: python -m venv venv
7. Run this in terminal: .\venv\Scripts\activate
8. Select the Python Interpreter in VS Code:
- Press Ctrl+Shift+P to open the Command Palette.
- Type Python: Select Interpreter and select it.
- In the list of interpreters, choose the one that points to the venv folder (it will look like ./venv/Scripts/python.exe on Windows.
9. Run this in terminal (installing necessary libraries);
- npm install react react-dom
- npm install axios
- npm install react-router-dom
- pip install fastapi
- pip install uvicorn
- pip install pydantic
- pip install python-jose
- pip install passlib[bcrypt]

Put the backend files on venv.

Running the project:
1. Backend (main.py under venv)
- uvicorn main:app --reload

2. Frontend (index.js)
- npm start
